context.question: okay what is the difference between those
context.answer:
In GFOS, "LES" (Leistungsende) typically refers to the end time of a service or task. It marks the completion time of regular work or service.

"SPL" (Spezialzeit), on the other hand, usually denotes special time entries that don't fall into the regular work category. This could include breaks, overtime, special projects, or any other non-standard time entries that require tracking separately from regular working hours.
